  <brief_title>Symbicort Single Inhaler Therapy for Asthma in a General Practice Setting</brief_title>
  <official_title>Effects of Symbicort Single Inhaler Therapy on Bronchial Hyper Responsiveness, Asthma Control and Safety in Mild to Moderate Asthmatics in General Practice, Compared to Usual Care Therapy</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>AstraZeneca</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>AstraZeneca</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective is to compare the effects of Symbicort SiT and treatment according to
      NHG-guidelines on bronchial hyperresponsiveness in asthmatic patients, as measured by PD20
      histamine, and to validate the Bronchial Hyperresponsiveness Questionnaire (BHQ).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
